photos.Observation Details: A small mixed flock caught my attention, I noticed a Chestnut-backed Chickadee very close to a Wilson's Warbler, something flew across my view and when I found it about 20 feet away I realized those birds were harassing a Northern Pygmy-Owl. I didn't realize til I got home and looked at my photos that it was grasping a dead bird. No vocalizations
